SCRAPIE, SHEEP - ROMANIA: OIE
*****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Wed 13 Jun 2007
Source: OIE Disease Information, WAHID (World Animal Health
Information Database), Exceptional epidemiological events [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=5565>

Scrapie information from Romania
----------------
Information received on 13 Jun 2007 from Dr Stefan Nicolae, Directeur
Generale, Direction Generale, Autorite Nationale Sanitaire
Veterinaire pour la Securite des Aliments (ANSVSA), Bucuresti ,
Romania
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 21 May 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 12 Jun 2007
Report date: 13 Jun 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Jun 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 08 Dec 2006
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Scrapie prion
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to Defined zone within the country
New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak Location: TIMIS (Hitias, Hitias)
Total animals affected
Species: Sheep
Susceptible: 17
Cases: 1
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 1
Epidemiology:
Source of infection - Unknown or inconclusive
Control measures:
Measures already applied
-Movement control inside the country
-Screening
-Vaccination permitted
-No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Stamping out
Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Institute for Diagnosis and Animal Health
(National laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species: Sheep
Test: western blotting
Test date: 12 Jun 2007
Result: Positive
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This is Romania's 2nd reported scrapie case; the first one was
discovered in December 2002 (see below reference). Scrapie is not
regarded a zoonosis. - Mod.AS]
See Also
